node.title: 'Bit of a weird one to celebrate': Jamie Whincup wins Sydney Supernight in Eastern Creek deluge
node.alt: Water sprays from the race track at night with super cars sliding in the wet
node.description: Race officials call all cars in with seven laps remaining as conditions worsen around Sydney Motorsport Park, giving Whincup his second victory of the season and the 124th of his career.
node.content:
["Jamie Whincup has taken the spoils in the final race of the Sydney Supernight after officials opted to suspend the race due to heavy rain.", "Whincup had a blistering start off the grid, jumping from sixth past teammate Shane Van Gisbergen in pole to first, before carnage ensued on the opening lap.", "Forecast\u00a0rain that narrowly missed Sunday's earlier race saturated the track, leaving Brodie Kostecki and James Courtney out of the race after they crashed heading into turn three of the opening lap.", "The safety car was deployed but Van Gisbergen overshot the straight on the restart, spinning out before being hit with a pit lane penalty later in the race for a dangerous pit stop.", "The championship leader finished 23rd, leaving Whincup to hold off Anton De Pasquale in second and Chaz Mostert in third on the way to his 124th career win, and second in 2021.", "\"Bit of a weird one to celebrate, wins don't come very often in this day and age,\" Whincup told Fox Sports.", "\"Obviously pumped for the win but at the same time, Supercars did a good job. Just the fact we've got to rock up here next week as well \u2014 we're in a position where we can't be tearing cars up.", "\"So, the driver in me says keep going, the team owner in me says that's the right thing to do.\"", "", "
Whincup negotiated the tricky conditions to hold off second-placed\u00a0Anton De Pasquale.(AAP)
", "Race officials called all cars in with seven laps remaining after Jake Kostecki's crash brought the safety car out again, and track and visibility conditions worsened around Sydney Motorsport Park.", "But the driver of the day was Chaz Mostert who began the final race at the back of the grid before clawing his way up through the pack to secure a podium finish.", "Earlier on Sunday, Anton De Pasquale maintained his stellar form by taking victory in race 24, thanks to a faultless pit stop by his Shell V-Power team, after beginning on pole with soft compound tyres.", "", "
Whincup is second in the championship standings after his 124th career win.(AAP)
